Oh, the light's back.

279
00:23:20,110 --> 00:23:21,870
I would like to thank our Korean partner

280
00:23:22,580 --> 00:23:25,300
for their trust in
Northern Thailand's agriculture.

281
00:23:25,770 --> 00:23:27,510
However, I would like everyone

282
00:23:27,540 --> 00:23:29,480
to take a closer look at this first.

283
00:23:43,460 --> 00:23:45,490
You are spreading misinformation

284
00:23:45,920 --> 00:23:47,960
and defaming Khum Rimpha.

285
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:49,870
Are you really going to argue

286
00:23:50,350 --> 00:23:52,310
with these statistics?

287
00:23:53,340 --> 00:23:54,590
Please let me finish.

288
00:23:55,680 --> 00:23:58,090
I promise the truth never hurts anyone.

289
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:01,500
Except those who fear it.

290
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:05,690
Manmuang, sit down.

291
00:24:10,050 --> 00:24:12,190
What you're seeing right now

292
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:16,420
is the actual export data from
Phusangdao Farm and Khum Rimpha

293
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:18,810
over the past five years.

294
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:21,110
This line graph shows the real trend,

295
00:24:21,500 --> 00:24:24,200
rather than just numbers
on presentation slides.

296
00:24:24,620 --> 00:24:25,620
And right here

297
00:24:27,010 --> 00:24:29,700
is the original partnership
agreement that I signed,

298
00:24:29,730 --> 00:24:33,500
which contains the actual data
we first submitted to K Group.

299
00:24:34,660 --> 00:24:36,280
And this is the latest document

300
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:40,420
sent to Mr. Hosuk and his team in Korea,

301
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:43,900
which does not bear my signature.

302
00:24:44,970 --> 00:24:47,610
All the figures also differ from
what we originally proposed.

303
00:24:54,060 --> 00:24:55,680
I understand that someone on our side

304
00:24:57,090 --> 00:24:59,690
altered the data before
sending it to Mr. Hosuk,

305
00:25:02,300 --> 00:25:04,600
without my knowledge.

306
00:25:06,060 --> 00:25:06,920
Isn't that right,

307
00:25:08,510 --> 00:25:09,510
Ms. Wipa,

308
00:25:11,860 --> 00:25:13,490
the illegitimate daughter

309
00:25:14,690 --> 00:25:16,000
of Mr. Montri?

310
00:26:02,810 --> 00:26:03,910
You can go to the crime scene.

311
00:26:03,940 --> 00:26:04,510
Yes.

312
00:26:54,400 --> 00:26:56,090
Then I have something for you to do.

313
00:26:58,400 --> 00:27:01,740
It is something that only you can do.

314
00:27:02,450 --> 00:27:02,990
Boss called us.

315
00:27:03,330 --> 00:27:03,810
Let's go.

316
00:27:04,050 --> 00:27:04,480
Yes.

317
00:27:19,710 --> 00:27:21,910
This is the key evidence

318
00:27:22,500 --> 00:27:26,140
that will leave Mr. Montri and
his illegitimate daughter, Ms. Wipa,

319
00:27:27,320 --> 00:27:28,200
with no way to deny it.

320
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:47,800
Well done.

321
00:27:57,490 --> 00:27:59,410
What is the meaning of this, Dad?

322
00:27:59,820 --> 00:28:01,460
I'm his child too, just like you!

323
00:28:03,740 --> 00:28:04,900
You're an idiot.

324
00:28:05,140 --> 00:28:07,640
Dad put you in charge of Khum Rimpha,
and this is all you can do?

325
00:28:07,960 --> 00:28:09,770
I'm the one who has to clean up your mess

326
00:28:09,810 --> 00:28:10,910
because of an incompetent son like you...

327
00:28:10,950 --> 00:28:11,620
Enough!

328
00:28:21,320 --> 00:28:22,520
Do you really think

329
00:28:23,040 --> 00:28:24,700
I see you as my daughter?

330
00:28:27,870 --> 00:28:29,900
Because you and your mother

331
00:28:31,300 --> 00:28:33,320
are nothing but worthless trash!

332
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:39,080
All these years,

333
00:28:40,810 --> 00:28:43,100
you've been forcing your way into my life.

334
00:28:46,240 --> 00:28:48,150
I only have one daughter...

335
00:28:59,120 --> 00:29:00,860
and that's Mueanphae.

336
00:29:08,620 --> 00:29:10,300
You only have one daughter?

337
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:19,000
Well, if she's gone,

338
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:20,750
will you accept me as your daughter then?

339
00:29:42,420 --> 00:29:43,120
Hey!

340
00:29:44,600 --> 00:29:45,600
Get her out of here.

341
00:29:46,830 --> 00:29:47,310
Quickly!

342
00:29:48,110 --> 00:29:49,910
- You'll have to leave, Ms. Wipa.
- No, no!

343
00:29:51,060 --> 00:29:51,800
No!!

344
00:29:52,110 --> 00:29:53,950
- Let me go! No!
- Quick, get her out of here.

345
00:29:55,690 --> 00:29:56,400
Ugh, no!!

346
00:30:02,010 --> 00:30:03,590
Quick, get her out.

347
00:30:05,910 --> 00:30:06,630
No!

348
00:30:07,260 --> 00:30:08,210
Let go!

349
00:30:15,610 --> 00:30:16,170
Let go of me!

350
00:30:16,610 --> 00:30:17,220
Let go!

351
00:30:21,990 --> 00:30:24,510
You got everything because you're his son!

352
00:30:26,540 --> 00:30:28,690
Dad, dad, help me!

353
00:30:29,620 --> 00:30:30,450
Dad.

354
00:30:30,710 --> 00:30:31,710
Dad!

355
00:30:32,770 --> 00:30:33,760
Let go.

356
00:30:33,860 --> 00:30:34,660
Dad.

357
00:30:34,690 --> 00:30:37,120
Dad, I love you. Please, help me!

358
00:30:37,150 --> 00:30:37,760
Go.

359
00:30:37,830 --> 00:30:38,470
Dad!

360
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:40,000
Let me go!

361
00:30:40,030 --> 00:30:41,680
Dad!

362
00:30:41,730 --> 00:30:43,730
Dad help...

363
00:30:44,190 --> 00:30:45,980
Help me.

364
00:30:46,120 --> 00:30:47,860
- I love you, dad.
- Are you alright?

365
00:30:47,890 --> 00:30:48,640
Dad!!

366
00:30:48,750 --> 00:30:49,490
Dad!

367
00:30:49,770 --> 00:30:51,930
- Dad, don't leave me!
- Was it forged?

368
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:53,500
- Was it really forged, Mr. Montri?
- Dad!

369
00:30:53,580 --> 00:30:55,240
Is she really your illegitimate child?

370
00:31:10,430 --> 00:31:11,620
Mr. Sila.

371
00:31:31,700 --> 00:31:33,830
We are truly sorry for what happened.

372
00:31:33,860 --> 00:31:35,300
We will review all the documents

373
00:31:35,330 --> 00:31:37,370
and get back to you with our feedback.

374
00:31:38,530 --> 00:31:40,190
I look forward to working with you.

375
00:32:13,700 --> 00:32:15,250
May the misfortunes be gone.

376
00:32:15,290 --> 00:32:17,520
And may good things come your way.

377
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:21,120
Our Phusangdao Farm

378
00:32:21,250 --> 00:32:24,040
has been through many bad things.

379
00:32:24,500 --> 00:32:27,520
Yet you have been treating us
with utmost care.

380
00:32:27,560 --> 00:32:29,920
That is why we are here together.

381
00:32:29,960 --> 00:32:33,660
May your life be filled with happiness
and prosperity.

382
00:32:34,060 --> 00:32:34,870
Thank you, Auntie.

383
00:32:34,900 --> 00:32:35,800
You're welcome.

384
00:32:36,100 --> 00:32:38,590
Come, now, Saitharn.

385
00:32:39,100 --> 00:32:42,060
You, too, have been through many bad things.

386
00:32:42,620 --> 00:32:44,850
From now on,

387
00:32:45,010 --> 00:32:47,730
since you were sent from the heavens,

388
00:32:47,940 --> 00:32:51,400
no matter what happens,

389
00:32:52,110 --> 00:32:54,400
whether it's good or bad,

390
00:32:54,500 --> 00:32:56,440
or whatever they are,

391
00:32:56,500 --> 00:32:57,500
you are

392
00:32:57,630 --> 00:33:01,970
part of our family here. You are welcome.

393
00:33:02,330 --> 00:33:03,850
May you find peace and solace here.

394
00:33:07,780 --> 00:33:08,930
Thank you, Auntie.

395
00:33:10,340 --> 00:33:11,580
I promise

396
00:33:12,090 --> 00:33:16,480
to work hard to repay Sila

397
00:33:22,110 --> 00:33:23,430
and...

398
00:33:24,260 --> 00:33:25,910
everyone here.

399
00:33:27,890 --> 00:33:29,700
Righto. No need to be so emotional.

400
00:33:29,730 --> 00:33:32,600
Next time, don't just pull the plants
from their roots like you did.

401
00:33:32,650 --> 00:33:33,700
Remember what you did?

402
00:33:33,920 --> 00:33:35,760
That was ridiculous.
I won't stop bringing it up.

403
00:33:38,740 --> 00:33:40,400
I, too, promise

404
00:33:40,970 --> 00:33:42,680
to take care of everyone well.

405
00:33:45,240 --> 00:33:47,000
And thank you, everyone,

406
00:33:47,210 --> 00:33:48,900
for dedicating yourselves to this work.

407
00:33:49,400 --> 00:33:51,840
I will do my best to improve our farm

408
00:33:52,200 --> 00:33:54,590
and become the boss
that everyone can count on.

409
00:33:56,700 --> 00:33:57,610
Alright, alright.

410
00:33:57,640 --> 00:33:58,780
It's our turn now.

411
00:33:59,450 --> 00:33:59,840
Come on.

412
00:33:59,870 --> 00:34:01,380
Please make way, Boss.

413
00:34:01,490 --> 00:34:03,350
Give us a very great blessing, Auntie.

414
00:34:03,390 --> 00:34:05,110
Don't make it sound too old like you just did.

415
00:34:05,170 --> 00:34:07,040
"Old"? Nonsense.

416
00:34:07,070 --> 00:34:10,210
I have been giving the same blessing
countless times now.

417
00:34:11,650 --> 00:34:13,580
I have already been giving
the same blessing many times.

418
00:34:13,889 --> 00:34:16,260
- May you find peace and solace here.
- Auntie.

419
00:34:16,300 --> 00:34:18,960
- From now on,
- Still the same blessings.

420
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:23,100
may you find happiness and prosperity
and be free from all hardships.

421
00:34:23,440 --> 00:34:24,370
Thank you.

422
00:34:24,570 --> 00:34:25,300
Come, now.

423
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:26,070
Auntie.

424
00:34:26,110 --> 00:34:27,530
That still sounded too old.

425
00:34:27,580 --> 00:34:30,730
- Bless me in the Gen Z manner, will you?
- One day, you'll be old, too.

426
00:34:30,750 --> 00:34:32,300
- Right.
- Oh, now, now.

427
00:34:32,320 --> 00:34:33,880
- May you find happiness here.
- It sounds really old.

428
00:34:34,130 --> 00:34:35,969
Can you give them blessings
in the Gen Z manner?

429
00:34:37,190 --> 00:34:38,320
- No?
- May you find peace.

430
00:34:39,420 --> 00:34:40,620
It's the same.

431
00:34:41,639 --> 00:34:43,000
What about me, Auntie?

432
00:34:43,889 --> 00:34:44,969
Give me one in the Gen Z tone.

433
00:34:45,010 --> 00:34:47,949
No, "May you live a long and healthy life," please.
None of that.

434
00:34:48,020 --> 00:34:50,330
May you find happiness and prosperity.

435
00:34:50,370 --> 00:34:52,330
May a wealthy man come your way.

436
00:34:52,360 --> 00:34:55,020
May you have lines of guys
waiting to date you.

437
00:34:55,060 --> 00:34:55,800
"Handsome guys," too.

438
00:34:55,830 --> 00:34:57,610
Yes, absolutely.

439
00:35:25,550 --> 00:35:28,680
So many people have come to the ceremony.

440
00:35:29,130 --> 00:35:31,480
In my whole life,
I've never been to a blessing ceremony.

441
00:35:31,520 --> 00:35:33,200
It's called "Bai Sri Su Kwan," right?

442
00:35:33,230 --> 00:35:34,700
I've never been to one.

443
00:35:35,520 --> 00:35:37,110
And there's so much food there.

444
00:35:37,360 --> 00:35:39,020
I'll make sure to enjoy it as much as I can

445
00:35:39,060 --> 00:35:40,280
so that it's worth the visit.

446
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:41,450
How's that?

447
00:35:41,830 --> 00:35:42,830
Have you been to one, Phae?

448
00:35:52,110 --> 00:35:53,110
Phae.

449
00:35:53,940 --> 00:35:54,940
Is there something wrong?

450
00:35:58,600 --> 00:35:59,600
Gale.

451
00:36:00,050 --> 00:36:00,780
I...

452
00:36:03,810 --> 00:36:05,100
I don't know

453
00:36:05,540 --> 00:36:07,560
if I should come here.

454
00:36:09,250 --> 00:36:10,300
Why?

455
00:36:11,900 --> 00:36:14,080
You're still thinking about what happened?

456
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:16,480
Mm.

457
00:36:16,780 --> 00:36:18,210
Dad and Muang

458
00:36:19,700 --> 00:36:22,070
did really terrible things to Sila,

459
00:36:23,210 --> 00:36:25,100
and I think

460
00:36:27,090 --> 00:36:29,580
I should hold myself accountable.

461
00:36:34,760 --> 00:36:36,920
You're this tiny,

462
00:36:37,580 --> 00:36:39,290
yet you're full of thoughts.

463
00:36:44,610 --> 00:36:46,800
There's nothing for you
to hold yourself accountable for.

464
00:36:49,210 --> 00:36:51,690
You have nothing to do with it.

465
00:36:53,100 --> 00:36:54,100
On top of that,

466
00:36:54,900 --> 00:36:57,490
the one at fault
has received the punishment.

467
00:36:59,030 --> 00:37:00,410
Yes, I'm well aware,

468
00:37:00,610 --> 00:37:02,010
but I still feel like...

469
00:37:03,140 --> 00:37:04,610
There's no more to that.

470
00:37:06,690 --> 00:37:09,190
Saitharn invited you here, Phae.

471
00:37:10,410 --> 00:37:12,690
Sila still adores you,
as he always has.

472
00:37:14,290 --> 00:37:15,690
The same goes for others.

473
00:37:20,900 --> 00:37:22,420
Believe me, Phae.

474
00:37:23,100 --> 00:37:24,780
No one hates you.

475
00:37:27,620 --> 00:37:29,100
There's nothing to be afraid of.

476
00:37:30,340 --> 00:37:31,400
I'm right here with you.

477
00:37:41,650 --> 00:37:42,440
Let's go, shall we?

478
00:37:43,520 --> 00:37:44,600
Others are waiting.

479
00:38:49,440 --> 00:38:50,100
Hi.

480
00:38:52,410 --> 00:38:52,970
Come, now.

481
00:38:53,160 --> 00:38:54,700
Let me tie the blessing thread on your wrist.

482
00:39:09,850 --> 00:39:11,630
I've known you since you were born.

483
00:39:13,610 --> 00:39:15,830
Why wouldn't I know
what is clouding your mind?

484
00:39:18,120 --> 00:39:20,590
Don't feel sorry
for anything that happened, Phae.

485
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:25,690
To me, my little Mueanphae
is still as sweet as always.

486
00:39:28,450 --> 00:39:30,280
Just like the first day we met.

487
00:39:35,540 --> 00:39:36,610
Sila.

488
00:39:37,790 --> 00:39:39,190
I'm sorry.

489
00:39:40,910 --> 00:39:42,900
I'm sorry on my dad's behalf

490
00:39:43,580 --> 00:39:45,380
and Muang.

491
00:39:46,610 --> 00:39:48,470
- I'm sorry for everything...
- Phae, Phae.

492
00:39:53,700 --> 00:39:56,510
There's no need to apologize
for something you didn't do.

493
00:39:59,410 --> 00:40:00,410
Remember this:

494
00:40:01,810 --> 00:40:03,600
no matter what happens,

495
00:40:05,120 --> 00:40:07,870
I'm still your brother, as always.

496
00:40:18,290 --> 00:40:19,090
It's okay.

497
00:40:27,230 --> 00:40:28,400
It's okay, alright?

498
00:40:39,680 --> 00:40:40,730
Phae.

499
00:40:40,770 --> 00:40:42,460
Come this way.

500
00:40:42,610 --> 00:40:46,080
Allow me to tie a blessing thread
on your wrist.

501
00:40:46,510 --> 00:40:47,410
Go.

502
00:41:07,820 --> 00:41:11,070
May you find peace and solace,

503
00:41:11,110 --> 00:41:13,350
and may you live a long and healthy life.

504
00:41:20,750 --> 00:41:22,330
May you find happiness.

505
00:41:27,120 --> 00:41:28,890
Here you go.

506
00:41:31,020 --> 00:41:32,350
Khao tom hua ngok.

507
00:41:32,550 --> 00:41:33,730
Please enjoy.

508
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:35,330
Boss.

509
00:41:36,770 --> 00:41:38,490
Does this mean that

510
00:41:38,830 --> 00:41:40,320
we have closed the deal

511
00:41:40,400 --> 00:41:42,280
about that, have we not?

512
00:41:43,210 --> 00:41:43,850
Precisely.

513
00:41:44,570 --> 00:41:46,810
I just signed the contract yesterday.

514
00:41:48,340 --> 00:41:50,650
But from now on,
you might have to work a bit harder,

515
00:41:51,540 --> 00:41:53,380
as we need a higher yield.

516
00:41:53,910 --> 00:41:55,040
But do not worry.

517
00:41:55,460 --> 00:41:58,000
I'll hire more workers
to balance the workload.

518
00:41:59,140 --> 00:42:01,410
Oh! That is not something
I'm worrying about, Boss.

519
00:42:01,900 --> 00:42:03,420
Hard work doesn't scare me. I'm ready.

520
00:42:05,200 --> 00:42:05,880
That's good.

521
00:42:06,640 --> 00:42:07,700
Please enjoy, Uncle.

522
00:42:11,300 --> 00:42:13,090
Hey, here's your khao tom hua ngok.

523
00:42:14,740 --> 00:42:16,290
I've only learned what it is today.

524
00:42:16,720 --> 00:42:18,000
It's my first time hearing its name.

525
00:42:18,610 --> 00:42:20,000
Auntie Nong taught me how to make it.

526
00:42:20,040 --> 00:42:21,260
That's when I realized how tasty it is!

527
00:42:23,000 --> 00:42:25,090
Let's see if it's as tasty as you said.

528
00:42:38,330 --> 00:42:40,110
I also helped make it.

529
00:42:40,650 --> 00:42:43,580
Aside from adding coconut and sugar,

530
00:42:43,770 --> 00:42:46,520
I also added a dash of love.

531
00:42:47,410 --> 00:42:49,600
I hope you can feel it, Boss.

532
00:42:53,070 --> 00:42:54,200
Deary me, Paula.

533
00:42:54,650 --> 00:42:57,460
Why are you trying to flirt with him?

534
00:42:57,600 --> 00:42:59,670
Just help me collect
the pedestal trays already.

535
00:42:59,700 --> 00:43:00,520
Huh?

536
00:43:00,870 --> 00:43:02,360
Why do you have to bug him?

537
00:43:03,160 --> 00:43:04,600
Oh, gosh!

538
00:43:05,180 --> 00:43:06,760
You already finished it?

539
00:43:07,010 --> 00:43:08,490
It must've tasted good, right?

540
00:43:08,840 --> 00:43:10,570
See? I told you.

541
00:43:10,600 --> 00:43:12,710
It's just my first attempt, too.

542
00:43:14,000 --> 00:43:15,410
Mm. It's tasty.

543
00:43:19,000 --> 00:43:20,390
Just like the one who made it.

544
00:43:21,820 --> 00:43:22,890
Hey, come on.

545
00:43:23,690 --> 00:43:25,580
What are you saying? It's embarrassing.

546
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:28,620
Eat up already.

547
00:43:35,200 --> 00:43:35,920
Whoa.

548
00:43:39,300 --> 00:43:40,490
Time flies, doesn't it?

549
00:43:41,900 --> 00:43:43,620
- Yeah.
- I'm about to turn 20 soon.

550
00:43:43,990 --> 00:43:45,700
Time really does fly.

551
00:43:45,890 --> 00:43:48,190
Come on. Let's celebrate you hitting 20.

552
00:43:48,360 --> 00:43:49,220
Let me measure your height.

553
00:43:49,250 --> 00:43:49,860
Mm.

554
00:43:50,910 --> 00:43:51,480
Uh...

555
00:43:51,520 --> 00:43:52,220
How tall am I?

556
00:43:57,640 --> 00:43:58,640
Uh...

557
00:44:00,050 --> 00:44:01,720
You're taller than I was last year.

558
00:44:01,750 --> 00:44:02,250
Whoa.

559
00:44:02,290 --> 00:44:02,750
Hey!

560
00:44:03,700 --> 00:44:05,500
What are you two doing here, huh?

561
00:44:05,590 --> 00:44:06,590
What are you talking about?

562
00:44:06,930 --> 00:44:08,680
I'm measuring his height, alright?

563
00:44:08,710 --> 00:44:09,380
- Yeah.
- Really?

564
00:44:09,950 --> 00:44:11,210
Oh, Saitharn!

565
00:44:11,640 --> 00:44:13,400
Come measure your height with us.

566
00:44:13,500 --> 00:44:14,800
What? No!

567
00:44:15,080 --> 00:44:16,670
Aren't these the kids' height marks?

568
00:44:16,700 --> 00:44:18,470
- It's fine.
- It's okay.

569
00:44:18,640 --> 00:44:19,710
No, I don't want to do it.

570
00:44:19,750 --> 00:44:22,080
Come on. You can do it. It's fine, isn't it?

571
00:44:22,110 --> 00:44:22,820
- Come on, Mok, hold him.
- This way.

572
00:44:22,850 --> 00:44:24,060
Come here.

573
00:44:27,880 --> 00:44:28,880
Get out.

574
00:44:30,110 --> 00:44:31,020
How tall is he?

575
00:44:31,050 --> 00:44:31,700
Paula, it's your turn.

576
00:44:31,810 --> 00:44:32,890
Measure your height after him.

577
00:44:32,930 --> 00:44:34,410
Come on, come on.

578
00:44:34,440 --> 00:44:35,300
It's your turn.

579
00:44:35,540 --> 00:44:36,760
- Let's see how tall she is.
- Why am I only...

580
00:44:47,800 --> 00:44:48,550
Phae,

581
00:44:50,500 --> 00:44:51,500
what's wrong?

582
00:44:56,440 --> 00:44:57,830
I'll miss you so much.

583
00:44:59,050 --> 00:45:00,620
I haven't even gone through the gate,

584
00:45:00,960 --> 00:45:02,000
and you already miss me?

585
00:45:04,050 --> 00:45:04,770
Well...

586
00:45:05,140 --> 00:45:06,930
I don't know when we'll meet again.

587
00:45:09,010 --> 00:45:10,800
Bangkok is not that far.

588
00:45:11,540 --> 00:45:13,010
If you miss me, come visit.

589
00:45:13,900 --> 00:45:15,100
Or...

590
00:45:16,140 --> 00:45:18,330
do you want me to come see you?

591
00:45:21,260 --> 00:45:22,580
You can't do that.

592
00:45:22,970 --> 00:45:24,500
You're there to work,

593
00:45:25,620 --> 00:45:26,540
so just stay there.

594
00:45:26,690 --> 00:45:27,510
It's alright.

595
00:45:38,720 --> 00:45:40,800
But I want to take care of you, Phae.

596
00:45:42,610 --> 00:45:43,610
Would you like to...

597
00:45:46,100 --> 00:45:47,100
come with me?

598
00:45:52,290 --> 00:45:53,940
Go work with me.

599
00:45:55,840 --> 00:45:57,300
Do you want to come?

600
00:46:05,440 --> 00:46:06,610
Of course.

601
00:46:07,660 --> 00:46:09,310
I really want to go with you.

602
00:46:12,420 --> 00:46:13,880
But can you

603
00:46:15,820 --> 00:46:17,100
wait for me, Gale?

604
00:46:25,310 --> 00:46:26,920
I want to stay here

605
00:46:28,610 --> 00:46:30,380
and finish what I need to do.

606
00:46:32,320 --> 00:46:33,900
Then I'll follow you.

607
00:46:35,660 --> 00:46:37,480
So when that time comes,

608
00:46:37,650 --> 00:46:38,970
you can be proud

609
00:46:39,350 --> 00:46:40,910
to have a talented girlfriend like me.

610
00:46:42,050 --> 00:46:42,730
Hm?

611
00:46:50,500 --> 00:46:51,680
Of course I can wait.

612
00:46:53,600 --> 00:46:55,010
I'll always wait for you.

613
00:46:58,560 --> 00:47:01,500
But you don't need to prove anything anymore.

614
00:47:02,510 --> 00:47:04,290
You're already the best,

615
00:47:05,300 --> 00:47:06,300
and I know that.

616
00:47:07,440 --> 00:47:08,030
Understood?

617
00:47:14,210 --> 00:47:16,410
I'm not trying to prove myself to anyone.

618
00:47:16,900 --> 00:47:19,100
I just want to prove it to myself

619
00:47:21,610 --> 00:47:23,700
and make my dreams come true

620
00:47:25,520 --> 00:47:26,820
on my own.

621
00:47:32,960 --> 00:47:34,190
Then...

622
00:47:34,760 --> 00:47:36,320
I'll always be here

623
00:47:38,480 --> 00:47:40,270
to cheer for you.

624
00:47:43,870 --> 00:47:45,420
Thank you, Gale.

625
00:47:56,190 --> 00:47:57,110
Do you have to go now?

626
00:47:58,140 --> 00:47:59,140
Mm.

627
00:48:00,100 --> 00:48:01,170
I have to go now.

628
00:48:10,820 --> 00:48:11,820
I'm off, then.

629
00:48:15,680 --> 00:48:16,680
Good luck.

630
00:48:49,920 --> 00:48:51,730
[3 months later]

631
00:48:51,760 --> 00:48:52,930
You're used to living there now, huh?

632
00:48:54,390 --> 00:48:54,980
Mom.

633
00:48:55,430 --> 00:48:56,430
Come on now,

634
00:48:56,900 --> 00:48:58,490
if you're worried about me, just say it.

635
00:48:58,580 --> 00:49:00,380
Stop pretending to scold me.

636
00:49:01,220 --> 00:49:02,640
I'm not worried about you.

637
00:49:02,760 --> 00:49:04,510
I'm worried about the others on the farm.

638
00:49:04,570 --> 00:49:06,630
If you cause them trouble,

639
00:49:06,750 --> 00:49:09,110
they might blame me
for how I raised you.

640
00:49:09,220 --> 00:49:10,870
Come on, Mom!

641
00:49:11,220 --> 00:49:13,700
I'm not causing any trouble, alright?

642
00:49:14,520 --> 00:49:15,350
See,

643
00:49:15,430 --> 00:49:18,090
I got promoted
to be in charge of accounting.

644
00:49:18,390 --> 00:49:20,050
In place of that traitor?

645
00:49:20,300 --> 00:49:20,870
Huh?

646
00:49:21,120 --> 00:49:22,120
How did you know that?

647
00:49:22,500 --> 00:49:24,070
Who wouldn't?

648
00:49:24,370 --> 00:49:26,100
It's all over the news.

649
00:49:26,250 --> 00:49:29,080
I'm glad you didn't have to give
an interview to that famous news anchor.

650
00:49:29,450 --> 00:49:31,590
I'm tired of answering my friends' questions.

651
00:49:34,830 --> 00:49:38,700
They sent me photos of you
wearing weird clothes from the news.

652
00:49:39,020 --> 00:49:40,620
Am I pretty, then?

653
00:49:40,790 --> 00:49:42,760
Fine, you're pretty.

654
00:49:42,790 --> 00:49:44,660
You probably got that from your mom.

655
00:49:46,610 --> 00:49:49,070
Oh, and what about your debt?

656
00:49:49,210 --> 00:49:50,550
It's been almost four months now.

657
00:49:50,600 --> 00:49:52,990
If you've cleared your debts,
just come back home already.

658
00:49:59,990 --> 00:50:01,760
Come on, Mom!

659
00:50:02,190 --> 00:50:04,190
I'm not even close to paying off all my debt.

660
00:50:04,820 --> 00:50:07,240
I'll probably have to stay here
for a long time.

661
00:50:07,640 --> 00:50:09,170
I have to go now.

662
00:50:09,440 --> 00:50:11,240
Boss called me.

663
00:50:11,630 --> 00:50:13,180
Let's talk again soon.

664
00:50:13,620 --> 00:50:14,300
Bye-bye.

665
00:50:20,850 --> 00:50:22,070
Yes, like that.

666
00:50:22,150 --> 00:50:23,260
If you're so sure, then come after me.

667
00:50:23,290 --> 00:50:24,540
We'll see about that.

668
00:50:28,540 --> 00:50:30,510
Mok, get back to work, you prick.

669
00:50:32,330 --> 00:50:32,980
Auntie!

670
00:50:33,680 --> 00:50:34,680
You're not surprised?

671
00:50:35,690 --> 00:50:37,140
Hey, Mok, wait!

672
00:50:42,980 --> 00:50:43,950
Oh, sorry, Auntie.

673
00:50:46,890 --> 00:50:47,900
- Take this!
- Ow.

674
00:50:48,080 --> 00:50:49,280
Come back and do your work.

675
00:50:56,300 --> 00:50:57,960
You've been here for a few months now.

676
00:50:58,620 --> 00:50:59,620
How's it going?

677
00:51:01,420 --> 00:51:02,600
Mm...

678
00:51:03,280 --> 00:51:04,280
How's it going, huh?

679
00:51:04,940 --> 00:51:05,880
Well,

680
00:51:06,350 --> 00:51:07,700
it's fun

681
00:51:08,590 --> 00:51:09,590
but exhausting.

682
00:51:10,790 --> 00:51:11,600
Very exhausting.

683
00:51:12,400 --> 00:51:13,450
Extremely exhausting.

684
00:51:16,020 --> 00:51:16,560
What?

685
00:51:17,030 --> 00:51:18,230
Why are you laughing?

686
00:51:18,510 --> 00:51:19,390
I'm this tired

687
00:51:19,480 --> 00:51:20,480
because of you.

688
00:51:21,450 --> 00:51:22,060
What?

689
00:51:22,610 --> 00:51:23,740
How is this my fault?

690
00:51:24,630 --> 00:51:25,630
Can't be my fault.

691
00:51:28,780 --> 00:51:29,730
So...

692
00:51:32,240 --> 00:51:33,970
am I close to clearing my debt?

693
00:51:34,070 --> 00:51:35,070
I want to go home.

694
00:51:38,170 --> 00:51:38,850
Oh?

695
00:51:39,800 --> 00:51:40,700
You're sad, huh?

696
00:51:41,730 --> 00:51:43,260
Just kidding.

697
00:51:45,100 --> 00:51:46,720
I've come this far.

698
00:51:48,890 --> 00:51:50,810
You're making me work this hard,

699
00:51:51,050 --> 00:51:52,740
so why don't you clear my debt for me?

700
00:51:52,830 --> 00:51:53,930
Please?

701
00:51:56,930 --> 00:51:58,410
Hey, hey, that's enough!

702
00:51:59,420 --> 00:52:00,320
Stop it.

703
00:52:01,320 --> 00:52:02,120
Hey.

704
00:52:02,700 --> 00:52:03,870
You've been here for a long time,

705
00:52:03,910 --> 00:52:06,620
so when are you going to call me 'Boss'?

706
00:52:07,720 --> 00:52:09,260
Come on.

707
00:52:10,120 --> 00:52:10,910
I'd rather not.

708
00:52:12,040 --> 00:52:13,100
It sounds creepy.

709
00:52:13,650 --> 00:52:14,530
Please.

710
00:52:15,970 --> 00:52:17,230
Try calling me

711
00:52:17,400 --> 00:52:18,500
'Boss,' will you?

712
00:52:19,300 --> 00:52:20,790
Hey, you!

713
00:52:21,140 --> 00:52:21,970
I refuse.

714
00:52:23,740 --> 00:52:26,200
Can I call you something else?

715
00:52:27,890 --> 00:52:28,810
Something else, you say?

716
00:52:35,850 --> 00:52:36,850
Something else?

717
00:52:39,100 --> 00:52:40,360
Uh...

718
00:52:43,440 --> 00:52:44,250
'Daddy'?

719
00:52:48,900 --> 00:52:49,640
'Daddy.'

720
00:52:49,790 --> 00:52:50,510
Ew!

721
00:52:52,540 --> 00:52:53,440
Please.

722
00:52:54,040 --> 00:52:55,180
Call me, Saitharn.

723
00:52:56,590 --> 00:52:58,220
Call me your 'Daddy,' please.

724
00:53:00,800 --> 00:53:01,880
Call me 'Daddy.'

725
00:53:07,630 --> 00:53:09,060
Oh, you.

726
00:53:09,800 --> 00:53:11,820
Okay, fine. You win.

727
00:53:15,300 --> 00:53:15,990
Ugh!

728
00:53:17,800 --> 00:53:18,400
Boss.

729
00:53:19,830 --> 00:53:20,420
Hey.

730
00:53:20,690 --> 00:53:21,770
Get back here.

731
00:53:22,520 --> 00:53:23,520
Watch it.

732
00:53:52,080 --> 00:53:55,000
♫I almost gave up on love♫

733
00:53:55,040 --> 00:53:59,800
♫I thought I would never find the right one♫

734
00:54:00,160 --> 00:54:06,980
♫But destiny led you to me♫

735
00:54:12,350 --> 00:54:13,180
Saitharn.

736
00:54:14,970 --> 00:54:17,180
From now on,
you are no longer my debtor.

737
00:54:23,490 --> 00:54:24,490
You are my lover.

738
00:54:26,530 --> 00:54:28,120
You are part of my family.

739
00:54:33,930 --> 00:54:34,990
Thank you.

740
00:54:37,100 --> 00:54:38,390
You make me realize that...

741
00:54:39,410 --> 00:54:40,100
that...

742
00:54:40,920 --> 00:54:42,150
someone like me

743
00:54:42,690 --> 00:54:44,780
also deserves a love like this,

744
00:54:47,920 --> 00:54:48,920
from you

745
00:54:51,860 --> 00:54:54,080
and everyone here

746
00:54:55,000 --> 00:54:57,000
who has become my friends

747
00:54:58,100 --> 00:54:59,790
and my new family.

748
00:55:09,200 --> 00:55:10,200
Saitharn,

749
00:55:13,970 --> 00:55:14,970
stay with me, will you?

750
00:55:17,520 --> 00:55:19,890
Stay here at Phusangdao Farm with me

751
00:55:20,200 --> 00:55:21,660
forever.

752
00:55:32,030 --> 00:55:32,640
Yes,

753
00:55:32,950 --> 00:55:33,670
Boss.

754
00:55:35,010 --> 00:55:40,780
♫I wanna thank you for making me feel♫

755
00:55:40,820 --> 00:55:44,370
♫Just how beautiful love can be♫

756
00:55:44,410 --> 00:55:46,710
♫Every chamber of my heart♫

757
00:55:46,740 --> 00:55:49,300
♫Will be yours from now on♫

758
00:55:49,340 --> 00:55:55,060
♫You're a godsent present from above♫

759
00:55:55,090 --> 00:56:00,960
♫I'll always belong to you evermore♫

760
00:56:01,010 --> 00:56:06,690
♫My heart will always be yours forever♫

761
00:56:09,560 --> 00:56:10,490
I love you.

762
00:56:13,080 --> 00:56:14,010
Right.

763
00:56:14,620 --> 00:56:15,620
I love you, too.

764
00:56:25,700 --> 00:56:26,890
What a big ring.

765
00:56:28,520 --> 00:56:29,520
Thank you.

766
00:56:29,570 --> 00:56:30,120
Hey.

767
00:56:32,270 --> 00:56:38,090
♫You're a godsent present from above♫

768
00:56:38,140 --> 00:56:43,920
♫I'll always belong to you evermore♫

769
00:56:43,950 --> 00:56:50,390
♫My heart will always be yours forever♫

770
00:57:16,900 --> 00:57:18,620
May I see your ID, please?

771
00:57:32,320 --> 00:57:33,590
Your ID, please.

772
00:57:37,160 --> 00:57:38,830
[Mr. Thiwachai Saelim]
[Date of birth: June 14, 2006]

773
00:57:52,360 --> 00:57:52,980
Yes!

